This is what we've done so far:
Channel Configuration Flow:

Connect DAQ → sends *IDN? query
Identify succeeds (response contains "AGILENT" or "34970") → gB_ChannelData appears
User configures channels:
Check the channels you want to scan (e.g., 101, 103, 105)
Assign each a type (A Jaw Line, B Jaw Line, C Coil, Ambient, etc.)
Enter gain/offset for calibration (defaults to 1.0 and 0.0)
Click "Start Reading!":
Reads which channels are checked → builds scan list from only those channels
Updates the ChannelConfig with the selected type name and calibration values
Those names appear in the table's "Channel" column (e.g., "A Jaw Line@101")
Fallback: If the channel config panel isn't visible yet (DAQ not identified), it falls back to the old slot-based selection (all 20 channels in the selected slot).

Duration Panel: Also fully wired — hidden until you select the Duration mode, then you can enter hours/minutes/seconds.

Try it out: connect your DAQ, identify it, then configure some channels and start a test!

What we need to do next:
